text: Kim Kon-il (born 19 October 1966) is a South Korean sport shooter who competed in the 1988 Summer Olympics and in the 1992 Summer Olympics. ==References== Category:1966 births Category:Living people Category:South Korean male sport shooters Category:Trap and double trap shooters Category:Olympic shooters of South Korea Category:Shooters at the 1988 Summer Olympics Category:Shooters at the 1992 Summer Olympics
title: Kim Kon-il
